comments.content: Could be a Frankestein-font with all letters except capitals /L and /T from [Liberty](http://web.archive.org/web/20140829110208/http:/www.myfonts.com/search/liberty)/ [Viant](http://web.archive.org/web/20140829110208/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/itfmecanorma/viant)/ [Reliant](http://web.archive.org/web/20140829110208/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/intellecta/reliant) and /L and /T capitals from an other script I wasn't able to identify.
The L and T might be snipped glyphs from [Edwardian Script or Alt](http://web.archive.org/web/20140829110208/http:/old.myfonts.com/fonts/linotype/itc-edwardian-script/).
